SYNOPSIS
        #include <websocket.h>

        void websocket_send(string|bytes message, int opcode)

DESCRIPTION
        Send a WebSocket frame to the current interactive object.

        <message> is the data to send. For text frames it should be a
        string (sent as UTF-8); for binary frames it should be a bytes
        value.

        <opcode> specifies the frame type:
          WS_TEXT   (1): Text frame. <message> must be a string.
          WS_BINARY (2): Binary frame. <message> must be a bytes value.

        If <opcode> is 0 (the default), the type is determined
        automatically: strings are sent as text frames, bytes values
        as binary frames.

        The current object must be an interactive object with an active
        WebSocket connection (websocket_query_state() == WS_ACTIVE),
        otherwise an error is raised.

EXAMPLES
        // Send a text message
        websocket_send("Hello, WebSocket client!\n");

        // Send a JSON message
        websocket_send(json_serialize(([ "type": "chat",
                                         "msg": "Hello!" ])));

        // Send binary data
        websocket_send(to_bytes(data), WS_BINARY);

HISTORY
        Introduced in LDMud 3.6.9.

